@Darren - Astro Pop popsicles absolutely, unequivocally do exist. Even if you, personally, cannot google them up (I just did and found them in under 5 seconds -- in addition to having consumed them, so the only reason I resorted to the Googles is because I was astonished that they would not turn up on a search. They most certainly do...).

The year in the ALUM clue refers to the fact that most ALUMs from whatever institution are associated with the year they graduated from that institution.

The clues are almost always more than fair.  The criticisms of them, on the other hand, rarely are.

