@Toni-Ann 

here, we call them constructors.

another term that sometimes shows up is "cruciverbalists", but I think that includes both makers and solvers.

@Randy 

I've more often heard it as "has down pat", as a sales spiel or recited poem.

"Hands down" I would use more as an expression of affirmation, stressing that something is true, as in, he won that game hands down.

@Crevecoeur Once again someone saves me the trouble of writing a comment and expresses my thoughts better than I could. Thanks, I'm lazy!

The northeast corner did me in and I even resorted to looking up SUMNER. For some reason I had him confused with the fort. 

I (kinda) agree with recent comments about the puzzles being too easy and here I end up stumped by a Wednesday.
